Please note that this SGS issue is a "Qualifying Debt Security" ("QDS") eligible for the tax incentives approved by the Minister for Finance. Among the incentives, interest on QDS issued within the period from 28 February 1998 to 31 December 2018 (both dates inclusive), payable to non-residents with no permanent establishments in Singapore is exempted from withholding tax. In addition, interest on QDS payable to companies and body of persons in Singapore is taxed at a concessionary rate of 10% (Financial Sector Incentive-Standard Tier Company will be taxed at 12% with effect from 1 January 2011). For debt securities issued from 27 February 1999 to 31 December 2018 (both dates inclusive), the withholding tax exemption will also be extended to non-residents with permanent establishments in Singapore, provided that the debt securities are not purchased using funds from Singapore operations.

Interest income derived by individuals from SGS is exempted from tax, except where such income is derived through a partnership in Singapore or is derived from the carrying on of a trade, business or profession.

The QDS concessions described above have also been extended to any discount from any SGS issued during the period from 17 February 2006 to 31 December 2018 (both dates inclusive); and any prepayment fee, redemption premium or break cost from any SGS issued during the period from 15 February 2007 to 31 December 2018 (both dates inclusive). Persons who are not exempted from tax are required to declare their income received from the debt securities in their income tax returns.

* Where the coupon payment or redemption date specified above falls on a day that the electronic payment system, established by the Monetary Authority of Singapore and used for effecting coupon payment or redemption, is not in operation, coupon payment or redemption, as the case may be, will be effected on the next business day when the electronic payment system is in operation.
